name: complete
description: Indicate that the actor has completed the object

name: start
description: Indicate that the actor has started the object. For instance,when a person starts a course, a course module, or a test.

name: interacted
description: Indicate that the actor has interacted with the object. For instance, when a person touch a component on a artifact.

name: launched
description: Indicate that the actor has launched the object. For instance, when a person launches a course, a course module, or a test.

name: help
description: Indicate that the actor has requested help about the object. For instance, when a person requests help about a course, a course module, or a test.

name: pressed
description: Indicate that the actor has pressed the object. For instance, when a person presses a button on a artifact.

name: released
description: Indicate that the actor has released the object. For instance, when a person releases a button on a artifact.

name: paused
description: Indicate that the actor has paused the object. For instance, when a person pauses a course, a course module, or a test.

name: skipped
description: Indicate that the actor has skipped the object. For instance, when a person skips an action on a activity.

name: viewed
description: Indicate that the actor has viewed the object. For instance, when a person views a course, a course module, or a test.
